Torvonnilous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 3:10:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equipment Help</span><hr size=1> Start questing for crafted armor. At your level a full group will be needed, but you will get killer experience from it. You will also enhance all of your stats. Many of the quest items can be obtained easily since no one loots the quest pieces unless they are warriors. Many times they just rot. Get a port to NK and you can hit SK for the Aviak charm, EK ot Gorge for optic nerves, NK or EK for griff eyes, and Runnyeye for the dorf runes.<br>
<br>
Be sure to should for them, many people will just let you loot since they are no drop and worthless unless you are questing.<br>
<br>
A full suit of crafted should get you well into the 30s and higher. I still see crafted on 40s and 50s that havent gotten lucky enough to upgrade to planar or velious armor.<br>
<br>
BTW - ran into a 46 warrior with full crafted the other day - AC was over 800. Not bad for armor that can be obtained in the early 20s. Also, expect to shell out about 1300-1500 for gems to complete the quests. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
